article.description:
Jarrius Jackson scored 21 points despite making only 4 of 17 shots, leading Texas Tech past Kansas State 73-65 in
the opening round of the Big 12 tournament Thursday and keeping alive one of coach Bob Knight's most disappointing seasons.
article.headline: Texas Tech continues season with win
article.linkText: Texas Tech downs Kansas State in Big 12 opening round
article.story: MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- David Hoskins had 29 points and 10 rebounds to lead Kansas State to a 94-90 triple-overtime exhibition victory over Division II Washburn on Saturday night in Bob Huggins' first game as the Wildcats' coach. Cartier Martin's basket with 3 minutes remaining in the third overtime gave Kansas State the lead for good and Martin sealed the win, hitting two free throws with 11 seconds remaining to make it a four-point game. Martin finished with 19 points, and Clent Stewart and Jeramaine Maybank each added 11 points for Kansas State. Paul Byers led Washburn with 26 points and 10 rebounds, Michael Williams added 17 points and Brady Sisk had 16.
